title: Kate Middleton to join husband Prince William for first official visit to Dundee next week
text:
Tweet 
Kate Middleton and Prince William’s engagements continue this month as the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge are set to carry out five royal duties in Dundee. 
According to Hello! Magazine, Kate and William are scheduled to visit the Scottish city on Friday, October 23. 
The royal couple will met young people who struggle with mental health issues. Lately the Duchess has been focusing heavily on the battle against the stigma surrounding children’s mental health. 
The publication also wrote that the royal parents-of-two will participate in a family fun day at the Dundee Repertory Theatre, and after that, they will visit Abertay University. 
Shortly after, on October 26, Kate, William and Harry will enjoy a glowing evening as the royal trio will make their appearance at the world premiere of the latest Bond movie, Spectre. 
On October 27, Princess Kate will also carry out two engagements: first she will be present at an event hosted by the Chance UK’s charity, followed by the 100 Women in Hedge Funds Gala Dinner at the Victoria and Albert Museum. Spread the rumor
